; A different LLVM parse error (an undefined SSA value rather than a bad opcode), so
; the `{:?}`-escaped error string in the diagnostic differs. Confirms the self-host
; reads whatever message LLVMParseIRInContext writes to the `errout` char** out-param
; and Debug-escapes it faithfully, rather than matching one hard-coded error text.
(defn m [] (-> i64) (llvm-ir i64 [] "ret $ret %undefined"))
